President Biden gave an update on the progress of the Build Back Better agenda and the ongoing evacuation efforts in Afghanistan. He highlighted the economic growth and job creation achieved through the American Rescue Plan and emphasized the need for long-term investments in infrastructure, affordable housing, healthcare, and education. The President also urged corporations and the wealthy to pay their fair share of taxes to support these investments. Regarding Afghanistan, President Biden discussed the evacuation mission, stating that the U.S. is on track to finish by August 31st but is prepared to adjust the timetable if necessary. He acknowledged the risks posed by ISIS-K and the tenuous situation with the Taliban, emphasizing the importance of continued coordination and unity among G7 leaders. The President also highlighted the commitment to supporting refugees and evacuees, both in the United States and internationally, and emphasized the need to remain vigilant against terrorist threats.